    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Feature description\n\nI use bash in vi mode (set -o vi).  When issuing a 'v' in normal mode, bash will launch what's in  $EDITOR which I assigned to nvim.\r\n\r\nnvim will launch in full screen mode which block my view to the content on the screen.   To edit the command line, I only need 1 line, but nvim taking 4 or so lines would be fine.\r\n\r\nThe behavior should be like fzf's --height option where it would open toward the bottom of the cursor and push the needed lines up if needed, that way I can still see most of what is on the screen missing a few lines toward the top when the cursor is at the bottom.\r\n\r\nfzf --height=4  # fzf's example",
